<p>This theory makes certain claims about the representations and
processing involved in information integration.  In terms of
representation, it claims that the characteristics can be represented
as single values on a psychological scale.  The theory makes no claims
about what other representations, such as semantic features, might
generate these values.  Thus, the content of the representation is
just the scale values of the characteristics, and the format of the
representation is "metric", i.e., organization by order and distance
on a scale.  In terms of processing, the theory asserts that the scale
values are generated independently, and that the integrated
psychological value is obtained merely by adding the two
characteristic values.

